==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stump-tailed
<hw>Stump"-tailed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having a short,
thick tail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Stump-tailed lizard</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a
singular Australian scincoid lizard (<spn>Trachydosaurus rugosus</spn>)
having a short, thick tail resembling its head in form; -- called also
<altname>sleeping lizard</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stumpy</ent>⟦br⟧
